The paper deals with a problem in stream mining, specifically classification under streaming emerging new classes (SENC). This problem is related to machine learning and data mining, which are covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. The proposed method uses unsupervised learning as the basis to solve the SENC problem, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the use of completely random trees, which are a type of decision tree algorithm, indicating that it may be relevant to the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper involves classification and model update, which are common topics in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of trees for classification may also suggest relevance to cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval), which often involve image or text classification tasks. Overall, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG, followed by cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.CV, and cs.IR.
